    <subfield code="y">00000 The contribution of isospin 0 and 2 cross sections to the integrands for the PV sumrule, Eq.~(1), for the difference of helicity two and zero cross-sections, $\Delta\sigma$. Note the different ordinate scales for these plots. $\int ds\, (\sigma_2-\sigma_0)/s~ds$ of Eq.~(\ref{eq:PV1}) is, of course, the same as $\int dE\, 2(\sigma_2-\sigma_0)/E$, with $E$ the energy in the center of mass frame.  The dashed lines are for $\Delta\sigma$, the solid for ${\overline{\Delta\sigma}}$ of Eq.~(6), {\it i.e.} with the Born cross-section difference subtracted. In this latter case the PV sumrule essentially requires no contribution at higher energies from these channels.</subfield>
